    <question>
        <stimulus>"The age of Jackson was the age of the common man. This is the age of the uncommon man - the specialist, the expert, the trained administrator... Democracy must be guided by expertise."
- Herbert Croly, The Promise of American Life, 1909</stimulus>
        <prompt>This view most directly influenced which Progressive Era development?</prompt>
        <options>
            <option letter="a">Professional bureaucracies</option>
            <option letter="b">Direct primaries</option>
            <option letter="c">Initiative process</option>
            <option letter="d">Recall elections</option>
        </options>
        <answer>a</answer>
        <explanation>Croly's emphasis on expertise influenced the Progressive creation of professional bureaucracies staffed by trained experts rather than political appointees.</explanation>
